<div class="meg-fandom-logoblock"><big><center><big><big>[[The Trailblazers|THE TRAILBLAZERS]]' LIE</big><br>Presented by the M.E.G.</big><br></center></big>We have had enough of the massive disinformation regarding the dimension debate. [[The Multi-Dimension Theory]] originated from a spam post in Backchat with no proof whatsoever, yet we failed to silence or delete it in time. Further supports to the theory will not be tolerated unless with proper evidence, and we are ready to debunk this once and for all.</div><span class="mw-collapsible" id="mw-customcollapsible-con"><br><center><span class="mw-customtoggle-con">>CONTINUE</span></center></span><span class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-con"><center><br><div class="fp" style="animation-duration:2s;color:yellow"><big><big><big><big><big><big><big>Phenomenon 90<br>Directionality</big></big></big></big></big></big></big></div></center>
= Description =
<div class="meg-fandom-logoblock"><center><big>PHENOMENON REPORT (EXERPT)</big></center>'''Directionality''' is a phenomenon that affects all levels in the Backrooms. Unlike most phenomena, wanderers can activate this phenomenon at will by performing a simple action explained below.<br><br>

It is found that if one follows a wall in any direction in a level for at least thirty minutes without meeting another person, it would gain new properties never ever seen before. The same applies to sublevels or anomalous levels.<br>

{{Blurimage|file=Br2.png|caption=Level 0 L as an example.}}
A photo of the leftside version of Level 0 is provided as an example. The walls can be seen vandalized with gibberish graffiti, differing from the clean yellow walls in the normal level. The floor tiles are arranged in a checkerboard pattern, unlike the carpeted floor in the original.<br>

This phenomenon is likely a result of [[Shifting Geometry|strong space distortion]], as it forcibly changes the layout and appearance of a level, despite the affected level not being known to possess space distortion, such as Level 1.<br>

The directions determine the new properties the level gains. It is currently unknown why this happens. Those areas are named '''"Level # L"''' and '''"Level # R"''' respectively.</div>
= Examples =
<div class="meg-fandom-logoblock"><center><big>PHENOMENON REPORT (EXEPRT) (CONT.)</big></center>'''Level 1 L'''<br>

{{Blurimage|file=Level 1 L.webp|caption=Level 1 L filled with balloons.|width=250px}}Level 1 L is the leftside version of Level 1. It is a Chinese-styled underground car park. Compared to Level 1, the interior is painted slightly whiter and the air is warmer. There are thin lengthy hallways accessible through doors, linking every room together.<br><br>

At random intervals, balloons can suddenly rush into the hallways from an unknown source, making travelling annoyingly difficult. If one tries to pop them, more appears at a faster rate, possibly trapping the person inside, thus suffocating them.<br>

False Puddles and Paintings continue to exist in this level as they are exclusive entities in Level 1, but no Facelings or Dullers have been found in this special area, leaving Hounds, Clumps, and Deathmoths the only generic entities to reside there.<br><br>

'''Level 0 R'''{{Blurimage|file=Level 0 R.webp|caption=Level 0 R.}}
Level 0 R is the rightside version of Level 0. It looks almost identical to Level 0, but it has an unstable nature. Object are sometimes "convulsing" or "missing textures".<br>

Entities like smilers, hounds, etc. are present in this location. They are found to be more aggressive than usual. They do not hesitate to attack when they see a target, no matter their physical capabilities.<br><br></div>
= Extra =
<div class="meg-fandom-logoblock"><center><big>PHENOMENON REPORT (EXERPT) (CONT.)</big></center>This certainly is a pretty interesting phenomenon, but it has no practical value. Major properties of the affected level remain roughly the same, no new entrances or exits would be generated because of this.<br><br>

Further investigations might be initiated if time and resources allow, but this is solid proof that the dimensions claimed by the Trailblazers are false.</div>
